Formula One Teams Discuss Possibility of Taking Stake, Independent Reports

-- B y   B e n   M a r t i n
-- 
2011-06-26T10:21:51Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-26/formula-one-teams-discuss-possibility-of-bid-independent-says.html
Formula One  racing teams are
considering acquiring a stake in the business, the  Independent
on Sunday reported , citing Adam Parr, chairman of the Williams
team.  The racing teams have talked about the possibility of
making a collective bid and discussions are at an early stage,
the newspaper reported Parr as saying.  -- Editor: Anthony Aarons  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ben Martin in  London  at 
 bmartin38@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Paul Armstrong  at 
 Parmstrong10@bloomberg.net . 